<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="iddbc27143-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1988—<ref href="/us/pl/100/242">Pub. L. 100–242</ref> inserted “Applicability” as section catchline.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1983—<ref href="/us/pl/98/181">Pub. L. 98–181</ref> inserted “American Samoa,” after “Pacific Islands,”.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1969—<ref href="/us/pl/91/152">Pub. L. 91–152</ref> inserted “the Trust Territory of the Pacific Islands,” after “Guam,”.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1960—<ref href="/us/pl/86/624">Pub. L. 86–624</ref> struck out “Hawaii,” before “Puerto Rico”.</p>
